In this statement, President Obama extends his best wishes to the Iranian people on the occasion of Nowruz, the Persian New Year. He acknowledges the opportunity for a new relationship between the United States and Iran, based on Iran meeting its international obligations. The President highlights the progress made in the negotiations regarding Iran's nuclear program, emphasizing the need for a comprehensive solution that assures the world of Iran's peaceful intentions. He also mentions the potential benefits of a diplomatic resolution, including economic growth and opportunities for the Iranian people. President Obama concludes by expressing hope for a new chapter in the history of Iran, with improved relations between Iran and the United States.